name: Probabilistic Superficial Fibre Bundle Maps
description: This data contains the maximum probability map of superficial white matter fibre bundles, in the MNI ICBM152 reference brain. These bundles were identified using a hybrid approach, incorporating anatomical information (from cortical regions of interest) and fibre shape (fibre clustering), from the tractography datasets of 78 subjects in the Neurospinâ€™s ARCHI database. The maximum probability corresponds to the voxels with the highest number of putative fibres going through.

publications.citation: Guevara, P., Duclap, D., Poupon, C., Marrakchi-Kacem, L., Fillard, P., Le Bihan, D., Leboyer, M., Houenou, J., Mangin, J.- F (2012). Automatic fiber bundle segmentation in massive tractography datasets using a multi-subject bundle atlas. NeuroImage, 61(4),1083-99.
